Program: Thinking Allowed
Title: The Poppy; Traveller Children in Schools
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03hwbrk
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 25 Nov 2013
The Poppy - a cultural history. Laurie Taylor talks to renowned archaeologist and anthropologist, Nicholas Saunders, about his account of the origins, history and many meanings of the Remembrance Day Poppy. From ancient Egypt to Flanders Field to Afghanistan. How did a humble flower of the field become a worldwide icon? They're joined by Professor of History, Joanna Bourke. Also, Reader in Education, Kalwant Bhopal, discusses her research into the experience of traveller children in schools. Producer: Jayne Egerton. Show less